track_notes: 4.4 mile hike with 1700 EG along FS Trail 135 and the Appalachian Trail from seasonally accessible Rattlesnake Gap (35.848, -82.944). The track includes a side trip to an unnamed grassy bald before ascending Bluff Mtn. Time permitting, I recommend this short side trip for the great views.
track_title: W4C/CM-035 Bluff Mtn via Rattlesnake Gap

track_notes: Take NC 209 to Garenflo Gap Rd which dead ends at a gate where the AT crosses the gap.  Take the AT south. It is a 4 mile, 2,300 ft climb to the summit.  A nice rock formation at the summit make a good operating position with plenty of trees to erect antenna.  Verizon cell service adequate. Dean ~ K2JB

2.6 mile hike with 1530 EG.  Parking for several cars (35.8454, -82.9339) on FS Road 96 across from gated FS road.  Take the gated road for about .35 miles and take a right on logging road.  This is 50-100 feet further than where the road is shown on the USGS topo maps.  The logging road intersects with the AT in Kale Gap in about .6 miles.  Take a left and follow the AT 1.6 miles to the summit.
track_title: W4C/CM-035 - Bluff Mtn via Kale Gap
